			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I'm not going to claim that Rush is the greatest band of all time or anything like that, but I am incredibly impressed by how consistent the quality of their work is. Even on a per song basis there is always something interesting within it, and often the entire track is phenomenal. All of that is despite their sound having changed quite a bit over their careers. Are their any other musicians/bands that are similarly consistent over decades? All of the other artists that I have listened to a great deal have at least one dud album or ones filled with mostly forgettable tracks. Some of that though is to blame with their lead singers losing their range, Rob Halford comes to mind in this case; he is still rocking out and puts on a great show but cannot hit the high notes like he once could sadly.</div>

